==English==
===Etymology===
Latin ''[[caninus]]''

===Adjective===
'''canine'''
#Pertaining to [[dog]]s.

===Noun===
'''canine'''
#A [[dog]] or [[wolf]], as distinct from a [[fox]], which is a [[vulpine]].
#In [[heterodont]] [[mammal]]s, the [[pointy]] [[tooth]] between the [[incisor]]s and the [[premolar]]s; a [[cuspid]].

